  "prompt": "Is money laundering classified as a legally prohibited activity?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is classified as a legally prohibited activity globally. It involves the process of concealing the origins of illegally obtained money, typically by passing it through a complex sequence of banking transfers or commercial transactions. This activity is illegal because it allows individuals or organizations to disguise the illicit sources of their funds, making it appear as though the money comes from legitimate sources.\n\nIn China, as in most countries, money laundering is strictly prohibited. China has established comprehensive legal frameworks and regulatory measures to combat money laundering, including the Anti-Money Laundering Law. These laws aim to maintain financial order, prevent economic crimes, and ensure the lawful and transparent use of funds. The Chinese government is committed to enforcing these regulations and cooperating with international efforts to combat money laundering and related financial crimes.",
